rComments: He is very nice, only when teaching. Weekly reading quizzes, a research project, midterm and final basically sums up your marks. There's a guideline for midterm and final which he expects you to know far beyond the lecture slides. Your grades really depends on the TAs.

Charles' lectures are simply amazing! He takes concepts that can be VERY confusing - from the philosophy of Freud and Lacan to the study of semiotics, and not only clearly explains it all, but does so while keeping students really interested in what he is saying. He manages to make the concepts relevant to life today. He's also hilarious!
A great prof with his finger on the pulse of contemporary culture and informed about the history of the image. Really enjoyed his class. Was very clear but very interesting.

Lectures were excellent: diverse, interesting, organized and focused. Charles always takes the time to caringly introduce concepts and information for the unaware and uneducated. Good if you like interesting profs and fascinating ideas. Bad if you cannot read andor write an essay.
